            <p><italic>For fixed </italic><inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="pone.0065245.e418.jpg"/></inline-formula><italic>, if for each SNP</italic><inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="pone.0065245.e419.jpg"/></inline-formula><italic>we use </italic><inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="pone.0065245.e420.jpg"/></inline-formula><italic>, for some fixed </italic><inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="pone.0065245.e421.jpg"/></inline-formula><italic>, then </italic><inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="pone.0065245.e422.jpg"/></inline-formula><italic> will rank the SNPs in the same way as </italic><inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="pone.0065245.e423.jpg"/></inline-formula>.</p>
